text.__SUMMARY__: Bambusa beecheyana is a species of Bambusa bamboo.
text.Synonyms:
Arundarbor beecheyana  (Munro) Kuntze
Bambusa beecheyana var. beecheyana 
Bambusa beecheyana var. pubescens  (P.F.Li) W.C.Lin
Bambusa verticillata  Hook. & Arn. [Illegitimate]
Dendrocalamopsis beecheyana  (Munro) Keng f.
Dendrocalamopsis beecheyana var. pubescens  (P.F.Li) Keng f.	
Neosinocalamus beecheyanus  (Munro) Keng f. & T.H.Wen	
Neosinocalamus beecheyanus var. pubescens (P.F.Li) Keng f. & T.H.Wen	
Sinocalamus beecheyanus (Munro) McClure	
Sinocalamus beecheyanus var. pubescens W.T.Lin		
Sinocalamus pubescens (P.F. Li) Keng f.
text.Distribution: Bambusa beecheyana is found in Southern China to Indo-China and Taiwan.
text.Description:
Bambusa beecheyana is perennial and caespitose with short rhizomes. Its culms are erect, allowing it to grow 600 cm in height.
